Murder-accused Sandile Mantsoe, who allegedly killed his girlfriend Karabo Mokoena in his apartment before placing her body in a wheelie bin and burning her remains, appeared in the High Court in Johannesburg on Monday, but will only go on trial in April after his matter was postponed The murder trial has been postponed to the 16 April 2018. Mokoena was only 22-years-old when she was murdered, allegedly by her forex dealer boyfriend. Mantsoe, the father of three children, allegedly killed Mokoena, burnt her body and dumped it in a veld in Lyndhurst, Johannesburg. He will be remanded in custody until his next court appearance. READ MORE: Sandile Mantsoe due in court today National Prosecuting Authority spokesperson Phindi Mjonondwana said after the court proceedings that the state had requested the postponement because some of the evidence was with expert witnesses, but they were involved in another court case in Durban. – African News Agency